wfAtmInterfaceNumber.name: wfAtmInterfaceNumber

wfAtmInterfaceEntry.name: wfAtmInterfaceEntry
wfAtmInterfaceEntry.description: The attributes for a particular ATM DXI Interface

wfAtmInterfaceDisable.name: wfAtmInterfaceDisable
wfAtmInterfaceDisable.description: Indicates when an ATM DXI interface is to be enabled or disabled. Disabling will disable ATM Access over this interface. The ATM Interface instance is NOT removed from the MIB in this case.

wfAtmInterfaceState.name: wfAtmInterfaceState
wfAtmInterfaceState.description: Indicates the state for this interface. The state indicates Not Present when the interface has been configured but has not been initialized. Init state indicates that the interface is in the process of being initialized by the system. Up state indicates that the interface is operating normally. wfAtmInterfaceCircuit.name: wfAtmInterfaceCircuit

wfAtmInterfaceMaxSupportedVCs.name: wfAtmInterfaceMaxSupportedVCs

wfAtmInterfaceVCsInUse.name: wfAtmInterfaceVCsInUse

wfAtmInterfaceDescr.name: wfAtmInterfaceDescr

wfAtmInterfaceType.name: wfAtmInterfaceType

wfAtmPlcpTable.name: wfAtmPlcpTable
wfAtmPlcpTable.description: The ATM PLCP Table - CSU/DSU Resident The PLCP object reflects information about either DS1 or DS3 PLCP framing status and performance. There is one instance of this object for every ATM DS1 or DS3 UNI. The PLCP object is separated from the other ATM objects for two reasons. First, there may be ATM UNIs which use physical media other than DS1 or DS3, and thus the PLCP object may not apply to them. Second, the PLCP object may also be applied towards management of SMDS Interfaces (SIPs). This PLCP object is essentially a superset of the PLCP object described in the Internet Draft MIB for SMDS (SIPs). It contains variables of interest to some ATM service providers and customers.

wfAtmPlcpCct.name: wfAtmPlcpCct
wfAtmPlcpCct.description: Identifies the DS1 or DS3 PLCP port for which this entry contains information. This corresponds to the Wellfleet circuit number

wfAtmPlcpPhysical.name: wfAtmPlcpPhysical
wfAtmPlcpPhysical.description: Identifies the OID of the first object in the standard DS1 or DS3 MIB

wfAtmPlcpLof.description: True if Loss of Frame has been detected

wfAtmPlcpLofCFA.description: True if Loss of Frame has been detected over the CFA time period

wfAtmPlcpYellow.name: wfAtmPlcpYellow
wfAtmPlcpYellow.description: True if PLCP Yellow (Remote Alarm Indication) has been detected

wfAtmPlcpYellowCFA.name: wfAtmPlcpYellowCFA
wfAtmPlcpYellowCFA.description: True if PLCP Yellow (Remote Alarm Indication) has been detected over the CFA time period

wfAtmPlcpStatus.name: wfAtmPlcpStatus
wfAtmPlcpStatus.description: The value of this variable indicates the PLCP status as indicated by the three-bit PLCP LSS code received from the remote end. Connected is LSS code #0, linkUp is LSS code #6, and linkDown is code #3. OtherCode means that one of the other five possible code values is being received. OutOfFrame means that the PLCP is in the out of frame state, and therefore there is no code being received.

wfAtmPlcpFebeSESecs.name: wfAtmPlcpFebeSESecs

wfAtmUniTable.name: wfAtmUniTable
wfAtmUniTable.description: The ATM UNI Table - CSU/DSU Resident The ATM User Network Interface (UNI) object reflects information about a particular ATM UNI. In particular it contains information, both configuration and performance, from the 'ATM' or Cell layer of the ATM protocol hierarchy. It optionally keeps some information on a per-VPI/VCI basis. It 'points to' its associated physical layer object, for example the DS1 or DS3 PLCP object. It also 'points to' the (one or more) higher layer object(s), namely the ATM Adaptation Layer (AAL) object(s) which further process the ATM Cells. It should be noted that in the ATM UNI MIB, the receive (transmit) direction refers to data received from (transmitted to) the ATM UNI interface. ** For DL200 and DL3200 there is only one ATM UNI per DL unit ** and only one AAL object (specifically VBR) per ATM UNI.

wfAtmUniAal.name: wfAtmUniAal

wfAtmUniSeconds.name: wfAtmUniSeconds

wfAtmUniAtmTransmits.name: wfAtmUniAtmTransmits
wfAtmUniAtmTransmits.description: Valid (non-null) ATM Cells transmitted at this layer and passed down to the PLCP layer

wfAtmUniAtmLineNumber.name: wfAtmUniAtmLineNumber

wfAtmVbrTable.name: wfAtmVbrTable
wfAtmVbrTable.description: The ATM VBR Table - CSU/DSU Resident The ATM Variable Bit Rate (VBR) object is one of several types of ATM Adaptation Layer (AAL) objects. The ATM VBR object reflects information about a VBR service carried by an ATM UNI on behalf of a DTE interface (e.g. a DXI). In particular, it contains both configuration and performance information about the Segmentation and Reassembly (SAR) sublayer and the Convergence Sublayer (CS). Each instance of the VBR object has only one corresponding DTE interface, and only one corresponding ATM UNI, although it may correspond to several VPI/VCIs within a particular ATM UNI. The VBR object optionally keeps some information on a per-VPI/VCI basis. It should be noted that in the ATM VBR MIB, the receive (transmit) direction refers to data received from (transmitted to) the ATM UNI interface. ** For DL200 and DL3200 DSUs, there is only one ATM UNI per DSU ** and only one AAL object (specifically VBR) per ATM UNI. ** For these products, the DSU does not perform the ** integrity checks for the VBR CS layer, and thus will not ** provide all variables for the VBR CS table. The Router/Host ** is expected to perform these checks and provide these variables.

wfAtmDxiTable.name: wfAtmDxiTable
wfAtmDxiTable.description: The ATM DXI Table - An entry in this table is either resident in the Wellfleet MIB or in the Digital Link MIB via the SNMP Proxy. The Component attribute determines local or remote residency. The ATM Data Exchange Interface (DXI) object reflects information about an ATM DXI interface between an ATM DSU and a Router/Host. In particular, it contains both configuration and performance information specific to the DXI (ATM) interface. Each DXI instance typically corresponds to several (ATM) DXIADDRs. The DXI object optionally keeps some information on a per-DXIADDR basis. Each instance of the DXI object typically has only one corresponding ATM -AAL object, but the MIB has been structured so that a DXI may have more than one. It should be noted that in the DXI MIB, the receive (transmit) direction refers to data received from (transmitted to) the ATM interface. With a 23-bit DXIADDR, the range of valid DXIADDR index values is 1 thru 2**23 inclusive. Note that the 23-bit binary DXIADDR field (with values 0 thru 2**23-1) from the Frame Relay header must be incremented by one to yield the DXIADDR index for accessing the tables in the MIB. The DXIADDR consisting of all zeros (with corresponding MIB index value of 1) is reserved for the DXI Local Management Interface (LMI) with the DSU. DxiAddr ::= INTEGER (1..8388608) ** For DL200 and DL3200 DSUs, there is only one ATM DXI per DSU ** and only one AAL object (specifically VBR) per ATM DXI. ** For these products, the mapping between the DXI (Frame Relay) ** DXIADDR and the ATM VPI/VCI is fixed. The LMI DXIADDR has no ** corresponding VPI/VCI. Otherwise, the eight most significant ** bits of the DXIADDR map into the the VPI (the eight most ** significant bits of the VPI/VCI), the fifteen least ** significant bits of the DXIADDR map into the fifteen least ** significant bits of the VCI, and the most significant bit of ** the VCI is set to zero.

wfAtmVclCongestionIndication.description: The desired state of the Congestion Indication (CI) bit in the payload field of each ATM cell for this VCL.

wfAtmVclCellLossPriority.name: wfAtmVclCellLossPriority
wfAtmVclCellLossPriority.description: The desired state of the Cell Loss Priority (CLP) bit in the ATM header of each cell for this VCL. For 'drop-preference', the CLP bit will be set if the internal drop preference bit is set.

wfAtmVclCct.name: wfAtmVclCct
wfAtmVclCct.description: Identifies the object which corresponds to the Wellfleet circuit number

wfAtmVclDirectAccessCct.name: wfAtmVclDirectAccessCct
wfAtmVclDirectAccessCct.description: Circuit number to use for this VC for hybrid or direct access routing

wfAtmVclMulticast.name: wfAtmVclMulticast
wfAtmVclMulticast.description: Indicates whether this VPI/VCI is used for multicast or single destination.

wfAtmVclMode.name: wfAtmVclMode
wfAtmVclMode.description: The mode of the given VC. GROUP - treats the VC as one of many vc's on a circuit. HYBRID - treats the VC as one of many vc's on a circuit for protocol traffic, but as a separate circuit for bridging. DIRECT - treats the VC as a separate circuit for all applications.

wfAtmVclDrops.name: wfAtmVclDrops
wfAtmVclDrops.description: The total count of packets above the SSCS layer dropped on this VC

wfAtmVclVcIndex.name: wfAtmVclVcIndex
wfAtmVclVcIndex.description: Driver-defined VCI for quick table lookup

wfAtmVclVcType.name: wfAtmVclVcType
wfAtmVclVcType.description: Type of VC can be either permanent or switched. Only permanent VCs can be modfied. switchedMux is same as switched but is included here to be consistent with wfAtmServiceRecordVcType

wfAtmVclXmtTagging.name: wfAtmVclXmtTagging
wfAtmVclXmtTagging.description: Tagging forward VC messages if peak/sustainable rates exceeded

wfAtmVclRcvTagging.name: wfAtmVclRcvTagging
wfAtmVclRcvTagging.description: Tagging backward VC messages if peak/sustainable rates exceeded

wfAtmVclOamLpbkCellInterval.name: wfAtmVclOamLpbkCellInterval
wfAtmVclOamLpbkCellInterval.description: This is the time interval between two consecutive OAM loopback cells in numbers of second.

wfAtmVclOamLpbkThreshold1.name: wfAtmVclOamLpbkThreshold1
wfAtmVclOamLpbkThreshold1.description: This is the number of consecutive loopback OAM cells lost before the VC connection is declared down.

wfAtmVclOamLpbkThreshold2.name: wfAtmVclOamLpbkThreshold2
wfAtmVclOamLpbkThreshold2.description: This is the number of consecutive loopback OAM cells received before the VC connection is declared up.

wfAtmVclVcGroup.name: wfAtmVclVcGroup
wfAtmVclVcGroup.description: The group of VCs this VC is a member of. All VCs in a given group will have the same VcGroup.

wfAtmVclServiceClass.name: wfAtmVclServiceClass
wfAtmVclServiceClass.description: The internal service class of the traffic this VC will carry

wfAtmVclServiceCategory.name: wfAtmVclServiceCategory
wfAtmVclServiceCategory.description: The service category for a connection. other -- none of the following cbr -- constant bit rate vbrRt -- real-time variable bit rate vbrNRt -- non real-time variable bit rate abr -- available bit rate ubr -- unspecified bit rate ubrplus -- unspecified bit rate + Note: May not be supported on all ATM-based platforms.

wfAtmVclVBRType.name: wfAtmVclVBRType
wfAtmVclVBRType.description: Type 1 VBR: CLP=0+1 cells are rescheduled by PCR or SCR according to the GCRA state. Type 2 VBR: CLP=0 cells are rescheduled by PCR or SCR according to the GCRA state. CLP=1 cells are always rescheduled by PCR. Note: May not be supported on all ATM-based platforms.

wfAtmVclXmtMinimumCellRate.name: wfAtmVclXmtMinimumCellRate
wfAtmVclXmtMinimumCellRate.description: Transmit (Forward) Minimum Cell Rate in cells/second. This specifies the minimum cell rate required by an ATM connection (the source is always allowed to send at at LEAST this rate). Note: May not be supported on all ATM-based platforms and/or service categories.

wfAtmVclXmtInitialCellRate.name: wfAtmVclXmtInitialCellRate
wfAtmVclXmtInitialCellRate.description: Transmit (Forward) Initial Cell Rate in cells/second. The ICR is the rate at which the source should send initially and after an idle period. Note: May not be supported on all ATM-based platforms and/or service categories.

wfAtmVclXmtRateIncreaseFactor.name: wfAtmVclXmtRateIncreaseFactor
wfAtmVclXmtRateIncreaseFactor.description: Rate increase factor (RIF) controls the amount by which the cell Tx rate may increase upon receipt of an RM (Resource Management) cell. The value is a power of 2 from 1/32768 to 1. Legal values are 0-15 (0==1, 15==1/32768). The default is 4 (2**-4==1/16) as specified by af-tm-0056.000. Note: May not be supported on all ATM-based platforms and/or service categories.

wfAtmVclXmtRateDecreaseFactor.name: wfAtmVclXmtRateDecreaseFactor
wfAtmVclXmtRateDecreaseFactor.description: Rate decrease factor (RDF) controls the decrease in the cell Tx rate. The value is a power of 2 from 1/32768 to 1. Legal values are 0-15 (0==1, 15==1/32768). The default is 4 (2**-4==1/16) as specified by af-tm-0056.000. Note: May not be supported on all ATM-based platforms and/or service categories.

wfAtmVclStatsIndex.name: wfAtmVclStatsIndex
wfAtmVclStatsIndex.description: Uniquely identifies the interface that contains the appropriate management information.

wfAtmVclStatsVpi.name: wfAtmVclStatsVpi
wfAtmVclStatsVpi.description: The Virtual Path Identifier (VPI) value of the VCL.

wfAtmVclStatsVci.name: wfAtmVclStatsVci
wfAtmVclStatsVci.description: The Virtual Channel Identifier (VCI) value of the VCL.

wfAtmVclStatsVcIndex.name: wfAtmVclStatsVcIndex
wfAtmVclStatsVcIndex.description: Uniquely identifies the virtual channel connection.

wfAtmVclXmtCells.name: wfAtmVclXmtCells
wfAtmVclXmtCells.description: Accumulated total of user cells transmitted for this VCL. This attribute is a 64-bit counter. Does not include OAM cells.

wfAtmVclRcvCells.name: wfAtmVclRcvCells
wfAtmVclRcvCells.description: Accumulated total of user cells received for this VCL. This attribute is a 64-bit counter. Does not include OAM cells.

wfAtmVclRcvSequenceNumErrs.name: wfAtmVclRcvSequenceNumErrs
wfAtmVclRcvSequenceNumErrs.description: Number of times data was being reassembled and a SAR Protocol Data Unit (PDU) was received out of order for this VCL. This count is valid only when the adaptation layer protocol is AAL 3/4.

wfAtmVclXmtOamCells.name: wfAtmVclXmtOamCells
wfAtmVclXmtOamCells.description: Count of OAM cells transmitted successfully.

wfAtmVclRcvOamCells.name: wfAtmVclRcvOamCells
wfAtmVclRcvOamCells.description: Count of OAM cells received successfully.

wfAtmVclRcvOamCrcErrs.name: wfAtmVclRcvOamCrcErrs
wfAtmVclRcvOamCrcErrs.description: Count of OAM cells received with CRC10 error.

wfAtmSigEntry.description: This entry contains attributes needed for ATM Q.93B

wfAtmSigLineNumber.description: Instance identifier. This value is the line number of the router.

wfAtmSigState.description: Indicates the state of the Q.93B entity

wfAtmSigMaxServiceUsers.name: wfAtmSigMaxServiceUsers
wfAtmSigMaxServiceUsers.description: Max number of SAPs (service access points) allowed for users to connect

wfAtmSigMaxPtPtConnections.name: wfAtmSigMaxPtPtConnections
wfAtmSigMaxPtPtConnections.description: Max number of simultaneous point to point connections allowed per port

wfAtmSigMaxPtMultConnections.name: wfAtmSigMaxPtMultConnections
wfAtmSigMaxPtMultConnections.description: Max number of simultaneous point to multipt connections allowed per port

wfAtmSigMaxPartiesInMultConnect.name: wfAtmSigMaxPartiesInMultConnect
wfAtmSigMaxPartiesInMultConnect.description: Max number of simultaneous parties in a point to multipoint connection

wfAtmSigMaxRoutingRegistrations.name: wfAtmSigMaxRoutingRegistrations
wfAtmSigMaxRoutingRegistrations.description: Max number of registrations / routing entries allowed per port

wfAtmSigMinBufferThreshold.name: wfAtmSigMinBufferThreshold
wfAtmSigMinBufferThreshold.description: Min percentage of buffer pool that must be free to enable new calls (sub)

wfAtmSigTimerResolution.name: wfAtmSigTimerResolution
wfAtmSigTimerResolution.description: Number of system ticks elapsed between successive timer events in tenths

wfAtmSigVpi.name: wfAtmSigVpi
wfAtmSigVpi.description: Virtual Path Identifier for the Signalling VC

wfAtmSigVci.name: wfAtmSigVci
wfAtmSigVci.description: Virtual Channel Identifier for the Signalling VC

wfAtmSigStandard.name: wfAtmSigStandard
wfAtmSigStandard.description: Sig Protocol Standard, Uni3.0, Uni3.1, or Trillium Symmetrical Uni (sub)

wfAtmSigInterfaceType.name: wfAtmSigInterfaceType
wfAtmSigInterfaceType.description: Network Interface type, either USER or NETWORK side (sub)

wfAtmSigMinVciPtPt.name: wfAtmSigMinVciPtPt
wfAtmSigMinVciPtPt.description: Minimum VCI number that can be associated with a Point to Point VC

wfAtmSigMaxVciPtPt.name: wfAtmSigMaxVciPtPt
wfAtmSigMaxVciPtPt.description: Maximum VCI number that can be associated with a Point to Point VC

wfAtmSigMinVpiPtPt.name: wfAtmSigMinVpiPtPt
wfAtmSigMinVpiPtPt.description: Minimum VPI number that can be associated with a Point to Point VC

wfAtmSigMaxVpiPtPt.name: wfAtmSigMaxVpiPtPt
wfAtmSigMaxVpiPtPt.description: Maximum VPI number that can be associated with a Point to Point VC

wfAtmSigMinVciPtMltPt.name: wfAtmSigMinVciPtMltPt
wfAtmSigMinVciPtMltPt.description: Minimum VCI number that can be associated with a Point to Multipoint VC

wfAtmSigMaxVciPtMltPt.name: wfAtmSigMaxVciPtMltPt
wfAtmSigMaxVciPtMltPt.description: Maximum VCI number that can be associated with a Point to Multipoint VC

wfAtmSigMinVpiPtMltPt.name: wfAtmSigMinVpiPtMltPt
wfAtmSigMinVpiPtMltPt.description: Minimum VPI number that can be associated with a Point to Multipoint VC

wfAtmSigMaxVpiPtMltPt.name: wfAtmSigMaxVpiPtMltPt
wfAtmSigMaxVpiPtMltPt.description: Maximum VPI number that can be associated with a Point to Multipoint VC

wfAtmSigT309.name: wfAtmSigT309
wfAtmSigT309.description: Q.93B - SAAL Data Link Connect Timer

wfAtmSigT316.name: wfAtmSigT316
wfAtmSigT316.description: Q.93B Restart Request Sent on Interface Timer

wfAtmSigT316c.name: wfAtmSigT316c
wfAtmSigT316c.description: Q.93B Restart Request Sent on Channel Timer

wfAtmSigTDisc.description: Q.93B SAAL Data Link Disconnect Timer

wfAtmSigT398.description: Q.93B Drop Party Sent Timer - Multipoint Connections only

wfAtmSigT399.description: Q.93B Add Party Sent Timer - Multipoint Connections only

wfAtmSigNumRst.description: Number of restarts to be retransmitted before link considered down

wfAtmSigNumStat.name: wfAtmSigNumStat
wfAtmSigNumStat.description: Number of status enquiries to be retransmitted before link considered down

wfAtmSigRestart.name: wfAtmSigRestart
wfAtmSigRestart.description: Q.93B send restart when the link comes up. (sub)

wfAtmSigDebug.description: This flag will enable certain debug messages depending on the value set. The values are as follows: 1 - disable debugging 2 - Signalling Status events 4294967295 - All of the above

wfAtmSigCallsSec.name: wfAtmSigCallsSec
wfAtmSigCallsSec.description: The number of signaling messages per second allowed to flow out of the interface (call pacing). Zero turns this feature off.

wfAtmSigT397.name: wfAtmSigT397
wfAtmSigT397.description: Q.93B Alerting or Add Party Alterting Received Timer

wfAtmSscopTable.name: wfAtmSscopTable
wfAtmSscopTable.description: This table includes the ATM SSCOP MIB record for Q.SAAL

wfAtmSscopEntry.description: This entry contains attributes needed for ATM Q.SAAL

wfAtmSscopLineNumber.name: wfAtmSscopLineNumber
wfAtmSscopLineNumber.description: Instance identifier. This value is the line number of the router.

wfAtmSscopAtmCct.name: wfAtmSscopAtmCct
wfAtmSscopAtmCct.description: Circuit number of ATM driver associated with this Q.SAAL instance

wfAtmSscopState.name: wfAtmSscopState
wfAtmSscopState.description: Indicates the state of the Q.SAAL entity

wfAtmSscopLowThreshold.name: wfAtmSscopLowThreshold
wfAtmSscopLowThreshold.description: Congestion is reached when % of buffer pool goes below this threshold (sub)

wfAtmSscopUpThreshold.name: wfAtmSscopUpThreshold
wfAtmSscopUpThreshold.description: Congestion is stopped when % of buffer pool goes above this threshold (sub)

wfAtmSscopArbitration.name: wfAtmSscopArbitration
wfAtmSscopArbitration.description: Determines if Q.SAAL initiates link connection or waits for connect (sub)

wfAtmSscopPollTimer.name: wfAtmSscopPollTimer
wfAtmSscopPollTimer.description: SSCOP Poll Timer. The Maximum time between transmission of a POLL PDU in tenths/sec

wfAtmSscopKeepAliveTimer.name: wfAtmSscopKeepAliveTimer
wfAtmSscopKeepAliveTimer.description: SSCOP Keep Alive Timer. If no pending SD or SDP PDU's transmit a POLL PDU in tenths/sec

wfAtmSscopNoResponseTimer.name: wfAtmSscopNoResponseTimer
wfAtmSscopNoResponseTimer.description: SSCOP No Response Timer. Max time between receipt of a STAT PDU in tenths/sec

wfAtmSscopConnectControlTimer.name: wfAtmSscopConnectControlTimer
wfAtmSscopConnectControlTimer.description: SSCOP CC Timer. Time between xmt of BGN, END as long as ACK not received in tenths/sec

wfAtmSscopMaxCc.name: wfAtmSscopMaxCc
wfAtmSscopMaxCc.description: SSCOP MaxCC. Maximum number of transmissions of a BGN, END or RS PDU.

wfAtmSscopMaxPd.name: wfAtmSscopMaxPd
wfAtmSscopMaxPd.description: SSCOP MaxPD. Maximum value of VT(PD) before transmitting POLL PDU.

wfAtmSscopMaxStat.name: wfAtmSscopMaxStat
wfAtmSscopMaxStat.description: SSCOP MaxSTAT. Maximum number of list elements permissible in a STAT PDU

wfAtmSscopIdleTimer.name: wfAtmSscopIdleTimer
wfAtmSscopIdleTimer.description: SSCOP Idle Timer. Timer used to determine when to enter the transient connection phase. Units in tenths/second.

wfAtmSscopStandard.name: wfAtmSscopStandard
wfAtmSscopStandard.description: SSCOP version switch. UNI_V30, UNI_V31 and UNI_V40 for now. Probably no more than this.

wfAtmSscopDebug.name: wfAtmSscopDebug
wfAtmSscopDebug.description: This flag will enable certain debug messages depending on the value set. The values are as follows: 1 - disable debugging 2 - SSCOP Status events 4294967295 - All of the above

wfAtmIlmiTable.name: wfAtmIlmiTable
wfAtmIlmiTable.description: This table includes the ATM ILMI MIB record for UME/ILMI

wfAtmIlmiEntry.description: This entry contains attributes needed for ATM UME/ILMI

wfAtmIlmiLineNumber.name: wfAtmIlmiLineNumber
wfAtmIlmiLineNumber.description: Instance identifier. This value is the line number of the router.

wfAtmIlmiAtmCct.name: wfAtmIlmiAtmCct
wfAtmIlmiAtmCct.description: Circuit number of ATM driver associated with this UME/ILMI instance

wfAtmIlmiState.name: wfAtmIlmiState
wfAtmIlmiState.description: Indicates the state of the UME/ILMI entity

wfAtmIlmiLowThreshold.name: wfAtmIlmiLowThreshold
wfAtmIlmiLowThreshold.description: Congestion is reached when % of buffer pool goes below this threshold (sub)

wfAtmIlmiUpThreshold.name: wfAtmIlmiUpThreshold
wfAtmIlmiUpThreshold.description: Congestion is stopped when % of buffer pool goes above this threshold (sub)

wfAtmIlmiVpi.name: wfAtmIlmiVpi
wfAtmIlmiVpi.description: Virtual Path Identifier for the UME/ILMI VC

wfAtmIlmiVci.name: wfAtmIlmiVci
wfAtmIlmiVci.description: Virtual Channel Identifier for the UME/ILMI VC

wfAtmIlmiInterfaceType.name: wfAtmIlmiInterfaceType
wfAtmIlmiInterfaceType.description: Network Interface type, either USER or NETWORK side of the UME/ILMI

wfAtmIlmiGetRetryCnt.name: wfAtmIlmiGetRetryCnt
wfAtmIlmiGetRetryCnt.description: Max number of retransmissions of the UME/ILMI GET request before link down

wfAtmIlmiGetNextRetryCnt.name: wfAtmIlmiGetNextRetryCnt
wfAtmIlmiGetNextRetryCnt.description: Max number of retransmits of the UME/ILMI GETNEXT request before link down

wfAtmIlmiSetRetryCnt.name: wfAtmIlmiSetRetryCnt
wfAtmIlmiSetRetryCnt.description: Max number of retransmissions of the UME/ILMI SET request before link down

wfAtmIlmiLocalOid.name: wfAtmIlmiLocalOid
wfAtmIlmiLocalOid.description: Identifies the OID of the first object in the standard DS1 or DS3 MIB corresponding to this ATM UNI port

wfAtmIlmiDebug.name: wfAtmIlmiDebug
wfAtmIlmiDebug.description: This flag will enable certain debug messages depending on the value set. The values are as follows: 1 - disable debugging 2 - ILMI Status events 4294967295 - All of the above

wfAtmIlmiNetPrefixTimer.name: wfAtmIlmiNetPrefixTimer
wfAtmIlmiNetPrefixTimer.description: Time to wait for a Net prefix before restarting UME

wfAtmNetPrefixTable.name: wfAtmNetPrefixTable
wfAtmNetPrefixTable.description: This table includes the ATM Network Address Prefix record

wfAtmNetPrefixEntry.name: wfAtmNetPrefixEntry
wfAtmNetPrefixEntry.description: This entry contains attributes needed for a ATM Network Address Prefix

wfAtmNetPrefixPort.name: wfAtmNetPrefixPort
wfAtmNetPrefixPort.description: Port which uniquely identifies the UNI (ie. InterfaceIndex or line number)

wfAtmNetPrefixPrefix.name: wfAtmNetPrefixPrefix
wfAtmNetPrefixPrefix.description: Network Prefix used on this UNI

wfAtmNetPrefixStatus.name: wfAtmNetPrefixStatus
wfAtmNetPrefixStatus.description: Status of Network Prefix (being used or not being used)

wfAtmTableDebugTable.name: wfAtmTableDebugTable
wfAtmTableDebugTable.description: This is used to display the contents of internal ATM tables in the event log, for debug purposes.

wfAtmTableDebugEntry.name: wfAtmTableDebugEntry
wfAtmTableDebugEntry.description: This entry contains attributes needed for debugging internal ATM tables.

wfAtmTableDebugSlot.name: wfAtmTableDebugSlot
wfAtmTableDebugSlot.description: Slot that we want to dump ATM tables from.

wfAtmTableDebugType.name: wfAtmTableDebugType
wfAtmTableDebugType.description: Slot that we want to dump ATM tables from.

wfAtmAlcDrvTable.name: wfAtmAlcDrvTable
wfAtmAlcDrvTable.description: This table contains line record entries for each driver responsible for the management and control of an ATM/ALC interface.

wfAtmAlcState.name: wfAtmAlcState
wfAtmAlcState.description: Driver state parameter. This parameter does not represent the state of the physical interface!

wfAtmAlcLineNumber.name: wfAtmAlcLineNumber
wfAtmAlcLineNumber.description: Index value used to uniquely identify an instance of a physical ATM port. This index is generally chosen by SiteManager and shall be used as an instance identifier for ATM MIB objects.

wfAtmAlcType.name: wfAtmAlcType
wfAtmAlcType.description: The type of interface. This attribute is an alias for 'ifType.

wfAtmAlcMtu.name: wfAtmAlcMtu
wfAtmAlcMtu.description: The size of the largest packet which can be sent/received on the interface, specified in octets. This attribute is an alias for 'ifMtu'.

wfAtmAlcSpeed.name: wfAtmAlcSpeed
wfAtmAlcSpeed.description: An estimate of the interface's current bandwidth in bits per second. This attribute is an alias for 'ifSpeed'.

wfAtmAlcLastChange.name: wfAtmAlcLastChange
wfAtmAlcLastChange.description: The time (in hundreths of a second) since the network management portion of the system was last re-initialized. This attribute is an alias for 'ifLastChange' in the MIBII System Group.

wfAtmAlcDpNotify.name: wfAtmAlcDpNotify
wfAtmAlcDpNotify.description: Data Path (DP) notify function. This function, when enabled, will disable the DP interface when the physical interface becomes non-operational.

wfAtmAlcDpNotifyTimeout.name: wfAtmAlcDpNotifyTimeout
wfAtmAlcDpNotifyTimeout.description: Data Path (DP) notify function timeout period. This value specifies the number of seconds to wait before implementing the DP notify function. A timer will get set to this value when the state of the physical interface transitions from operational to non-operational when the DP notify function is enabled.

wfAtmAlcConfControlQSize.name: wfAtmAlcConfControlQSize
wfAtmAlcConfControlQSize.description: Number of command elements in each of the two Host Interface control qs

wfAtmAlcConfIntqSize.name: wfAtmAlcConfIntqSize
wfAtmAlcConfIntqSize.description: Number of elements in the Host Interface interrupt queue

wfAtmAlcConfLogqSize.name: wfAtmAlcConfLogqSize
wfAtmAlcConfLogqSize.description: Number of elements in the Host Interface log queue

wfAtmAlcConfNumXmtQueues.name: wfAtmAlcConfNumXmtQueues
wfAtmAlcConfNumXmtQueues.description: Number of transmit queues in the Host Interface between the Host Driver and the CoP Driver

wfAtmAlcUseDebugger.name: wfAtmAlcUseDebugger
wfAtmAlcUseDebugger.description: This attribute controls a debugger which may be built into the Coprocessor image. Shipped code does not include this debugger.

wfAtmAlcConfXmtClipSlotMax.name: wfAtmAlcConfXmtClipSlotMax
wfAtmAlcConfXmtClipSlotMax.description: Number of frames the slot may queue up for transmit before the Host Driver begins to clip. Setting this attribute forces the driver to use the non zero value of the attribute rather than selecting a clip point automatically.

wfAtmAlcXmtClipSlotMax.name: wfAtmAlcXmtClipSlotMax
wfAtmAlcXmtClipSlotMax.description: Number of buffers per slot beyond which the driver will clip on transmit. Set by the driver. May be forced by setting wfAtmAlcConfXmtClipSlotMax != 0

wfAtmAlcConfXmtClipQueueMax.name: wfAtmAlcConfXmtClipQueueMax
wfAtmAlcConfXmtClipQueueMax.description: Number of frames a transmit queue may queue up before the Host Driver begins to clip. Setting this attribute forces the driver to use the non zero value of the attribute rather than selecting a clip point automatically.

wfAtmAlcXmtClipQueueMax.name: wfAtmAlcXmtClipQueueMax
wfAtmAlcXmtClipQueueMax.description: Number of buffers per transmit queue beyond which the driver will clip on transmit. Set by the driver. May be forced by setting wfAtmAlcConfXmtClipQueueMax != 0

wfAtmAlcConfXmtClipQueueMin.name: wfAtmAlcConfXmtClipQueueMin
wfAtmAlcConfXmtClipQueueMin.description: Number of frames a transmit queue will always be permitted to queue up regardless of the current value of wfAtmOutQLen relative to wfAtmXmtClipSlotMax. Setting this attribute forces the driver to use the nonzero value of the attribute rather than selecting a clip point automatically.

wfAtmAlcXmtClipQueueMin.name: wfAtmAlcXmtClipQueueMin
wfAtmAlcXmtClipQueueMin.description: Number of buffers each transmit queue is guaranteed to get before the driver clips due to the value of wfAtmXmtClipSlotMax. Set by the driver. May be forced by setting wfAtmAlcConfXmtClipQueueMin != 0

wfAtmAlcXmtQueueBurst.name: wfAtmAlcXmtQueueBurst
wfAtmAlcXmtQueueBurst.description: Burst count for all transmit queues in CoP. Specifies the number of buffer(ettes) the CoP will process from a transmit queue in one service opportunity. A value of 0 (zero) will cause the CoP to burst forever (i.e., until either all data is transmitted from the queue or no more buffer(ette)s are available to transmit into.

wfAtmAlcXmtPackets.name: wfAtmAlcXmtPackets
wfAtmAlcXmtPackets.description: Count of Service Data Units (SDUs) transmitted without error.

wfAtmAlcXmtPacketClips.name: wfAtmAlcXmtPacketClips
wfAtmAlcXmtPacketClips.description: Count of packets dropped on transmit.

wfAtmAlcXmtOctets.name: wfAtmAlcXmtOctets
wfAtmAlcXmtOctets.description: Count of octets transmitted without error over the link interface. These octets are associated with user data only and not overhead or padding octets.

wfAtmAlcOutQLen.name: wfAtmAlcOutQLen
wfAtmAlcOutQLen.description: This attribute is an alias for 'ifOutQLen' in the MIBII interface group.

wfAtmAlcRcvPackets.name: wfAtmAlcRcvPackets
wfAtmAlcRcvPackets.description: Count of Service Data Units (SDUs) received without error.

wfAtmAlcRcvReplenMisses.name: wfAtmAlcRcvReplenMisses
wfAtmAlcRcvReplenMisses.description: Number of packet buffer misses while attempting to replenish driver receive ring.

wfAtmAlcConfRcvBuffersMax.name: wfAtmAlcConfRcvBuffersMax
wfAtmAlcConfRcvBuffersMax.description: Number of buffers the driver will try to maintain on its receive queue. Setting this attribute forces the driver to use the non zero value of the attribute rather than selecting a buffer count automatically.

wfAtmAlcRcvBuffersMax.name: wfAtmAlcRcvBuffersMax
wfAtmAlcRcvBuffersMax.description: Number of buffers which the driver will attempt to maintain on the receive queue. Set by the driver. May be forced by setting wfAtmAlcConfRcvBuffersMax != 0

wfAtmAlcMadr.name: wfAtmAlcMadr
wfAtmAlcMadr.description: First MAC address in canonical format (i.e., 00-00-a2...). The number of subsequent MAC addresses is specified by wfAtmAlcMadrCt which are sequential.

wfAtmizerDrvCfgVcInactEnable.name: wfAtmizerDrvCfgVcInactEnable

wfAtmizerDrvCfgFramingMode.name: wfAtmizerDrvCfgFramingMode

wfAtmizerDrvCfgClkSource.name: wfAtmizerDrvCfgClkSource

If a bit is cleared, it disables logging of an event class. ----------------------------------- | | ----------------------------------- 31 0 bit 0 - Link Module Coprocessor debug events bit 1 - VC setup/teardown events

wfAtmizerDrvCfgDsx3SendCode.name: wfAtmizerDrvCfgDsx3SendCode
wfAtmizerDrvCfgDsx3SendCode.description: This variable indicates what type of code is being sent across DS3/E3 interface by the device. (These are optional for E3 interfaces.) The values mean: ATM_DSX3_SEND_CODE_NONE : Sending looped or normal data. ATM_DSX3_SEND_CODE_LINE : Sending a request for line loopback. ATM_DSX3_SEND_CODE_PAYLOAD : Sending a request for a payload loopback. (i.e., all Ds1/E1s in a DS3/E3 frame) ATM_DSX3_SEND_CODE_RESET : Sending a loopback deactivation request. ATM_DSX3_SEND_CODE_DS1_LOOP: Requesting to loopback a particular DS1/E1 within a DS3/E3 frame. ATM_DSX3_SEND_TEST_PATTERN : Sending a test pattern.

wfAtmizerDrvCfgDsx3LoopbackConfig.name: wfAtmizerDrvCfgDsx3LoopbackConfig
wfAtmizerDrvCfgDsx3LoopbackConfig.description: This variable represents the loopback configuration of the DS3/E3 interface. Ther values mean: ATM_DSX3_LOOPBACK_NONE : Not in the loopback state/ A device that is not capable of performing a loopback on the interface shall always return this as it's value. ATM_DSX3_LOOPBACK_PAYLOAD : The received signal at this interface is looped through the device. Typically the received signal is looped back for retransmission after it has passed through the device's framing function. ATM_DSX3_LOOPBACK_LINE : The received signal at this interface does not go through the device (minimum penetration) but is looped back out. ATM_DSX3_LOOPBACK_OTHER : Loopback's that are not defined here.
